snippet.title: Young Jonn  - Cash Flow (feat. Wizkid) [Official Music Video]
snippet.description:
After back-to-back hits, Young Jonn returns with “Cash Flow” featuring Wizkid — a smooth anthem about living life soft, enjoying the fruits of success, and spending with ease. Opening with the reflective line “had a hard life but I live soft,” the track captures the transition from struggle to abundance, wrapped in Young Jonn’s jiggy energy and Wizkid’s signature calm delivery.

“Cash Flow” is more than a flex — it’s a celebration of growth, freedom, and the soft life. The record leads directly into Young Jonn’s highly anticipated project, Blue Disco, marking a new chapter in his sound and story.

🔵 Stream “Cash Flow” everywhere - https://youngjonn.lnk.to/cashflow

Instagram - https://bit.ly/3IeRruq

About Young Jonn
John Saviours Udomboso, fondly known as Young Jonn "The Wicked Producer" is an award winning Afro-pop producer, singer/songwriter. Dubbed the Sound of the Streets, "Young Jonn" is the head huncho and musical genius behind some of the most memorable Artists that own the streets in the Street-Hop or Pop genre. With over 3 awards in some of the prestigious Awards in Nigeria, Young Jonn's sound, lyrics and beats have broken several legendary Artists on the Nigerian music scene since the mid-2000s. snippet.title: YOU, ME & TUSCANY | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
You, Me & Tuscany - In Theaters April 10

Sometimes the wrong place is right where you need to be. 

From Will Packer, the blockbuster producer of Girls Trip, the Ride Along franchise, and ten movies that have opened No. 1 at the U.S. box office—including Night School, This Christmas and Think Like a Man—comes a delicious romantic comedy about one little lie, one large Italian villa, and two people getting lost in the sauce of love. 

Halle Bailey (The Little Mermaid, The Color Purple) stars as Anna, a young woman who has abandoned her dreams of becoming a chef and is now drifting through her twenties with a series of bad choices. When Anna loses her house-sitting job (and housing) in one fell swoop, a chance encounter with Matteo—a handsome Italian who happens to have a villa sitting empty in Tuscany—will inspire her to jet off for Italy, against the advice of her always-honest bestie, Claire (Home Before Dark’s Aziza Scott).  

But Anna’s plan to crash at Matteo’s villa, without permission, just for one night, falls apart when Matteo’s mother, Gabriella (Italian film icon Isabella Ferrari) shows up at the house unexpectedly. In a panic, Anna allows Gabriella to believe that she is Matteo’s fiancée. 

That little lie becomes a big problem, though, when Matteo’s cousin, Michael (Regé-Jean Page; Bridgerton, Black Bag) shows up, and Anna discovers that the heat between them may ignite a fire that will transform her life. 

The film’s international cast includes Lorenzo de Moor (The Legend Hunters) as Matteo, Marco Calvani (The Four Seasons) as an Italian taxi driver who befriends Anna and Academy Award® nominee Nia Vardalos (My Big Fat Greek Wedding) as Anna’s house-sitting client, Mrs. Dunn.  

You, Me & Tuscany is directed by acclaimed filmmaker Kat Coiro (Marry Me, Matlock), from a screenplay by Ryan Engle (Rampage, Beast), based on an original idea by Ryan Engle and Kristin Engle. The film is produced by Will Packer (Girls Trip, Ride Along films) and Johanna Byer (Point Blank, executive producer Praise This) for Will Packer Productions. The executive producers are Ryan Engle and Kristin Engle.

Korean ก่อ กรวิก (ออฟ จุมพล) นักธุรกิจสตาร์ตอัปผู้เกลียดการเจอผู้คน จนกระทั่งวันหนึ่งเขาได้พบกับ จิระ (กัน อรรถพันธ์) ศิลปินหนุ่มตกงานที่กำลังค้นหาตัวตน ด้วยแรงดึงดูดอันแปลกประหลาดทำให้ก่อตัดสินใจจ้างจิระมาสวมบทเป็น ‘มิสเตอร์เค’ ตัวแทนเจรจาธุรกิจ เพื่อแลกกับเงื่อนไขที่ดูเรียบง่ายอย่างการที่ก่อต้องมาเป็นแบบในภาพวาดของจิระ
 แต่เมื่อร่างกายเริ่มเข้าใกล้ เส้นแบ่งระหว่างแรงบันดาลใจกับแรงปรารถนาก็เริ่มพร่าเลือน...
จากนายจ้างกลายเป็นสัมพันธ์ต้องห้ามที่ทั้งร้อนแรงและซับซ้อน ก่อจุดไฟให้งานศิลปะของจิระ ในขณะเดียวกันจิระก็จุดไฟในใจเขา และยิ่งไฟนั้นลุกแรงเท่าไรก่อก็ตระหนักได้ว่าคนที่พร้อมจะเผาไหม้ไปด้วยกันอาจไม่ใช่แค่พวกเขาสองคน ทว่ายังมีเพื่อนสนิทอย่าง ภีม (ดิว จิรวรรตน์) ที่กำลังก้าวเข้ามาเป็นคู่แข่งในเกมรักครั้งนี้ด้วยหัวใจที่พร้อมเดิมพันเช่นเดียวกัน
 “ท่ามกลางความแนบชิดของคนสองสามคน จิระยังคงสับสนในความสัมพันธ์ระหว่างเขากับก่อและตัวเขากับภีมแบบไหนคือความรักที่ต้องการจากใจจริงกันแน่”  ติดตามได้ใน Burnout Syndrome ภาวะรักคนหมดไฟ ทุกวันพุธ เวลา 20:30 น. ทางช่อง GMM25 และดูออนไลน์ เวลา 21:30 น. บนแอป iQIYI และเว็บ iQ.com ที่เดียวเท่านั้น เริ่ม 26 พฤศจิกายนนี้

snippet.title: The Old Woman With The Knife - Official Trailer (2025) Lee Hye-young, Kim Sung-cheol
snippet.description:
Check out The Old Woman With The Knife trailer for the upcoming action movie starring Lee Hye-young, Kim Sung-cheol, and Kim Mu-yeol. 

Aging assassin Hornclaw has seen it all, but she never expected to mentor a reckless rookie like Bullfight. As their unlikely bond deepens, cracks form in the underworld they navigate together. When Hornclaw discovers someone wants her dead, she’s thrust into a deadly game of deception. With enemies closing in and trust in short supply, survival means staying sharp—both blade and mind.

The Old Woman With The Knife, directed by Kyu-dong Min, will be available on digital and physical November 25, 2025.

localized.title: The Old Woman With The Knife - Official Trailer (2025) Lee Hye-young, Kim Sung-cheol
localized.description:
Check out The Old Woman With The Knife trailer for the upcoming action movie starring Lee Hye-young, Kim Sung-cheol, and Kim Mu-yeol. 

Aging assassin Hornclaw has seen it all, but she never expected to mentor a reckless rookie like Bullfight. As their unlikely bond deepens, cracks form in the underworld they navigate together. When Hornclaw discovers someone wants her dead, she’s thrust into a deadly game of deception. With enemies closing in and trust in short supply, survival means staying sharp—both blade and mind.

The Old Woman With The Knife, directed by Kyu-dong Min, will be available on digital and physical November 25, 2025.

snippet.title: 10DANCE | Official Trailer | Netflix
snippet.description:
Pride clashes and bodies entwine as two polar opposites are drawn together by love and breathtaking dance.

Inouesatoh's hit manga "10 DANCE" depicts the passion, anguish, jealousy and love shared between two men wholly devoted to dance. Now, this sweetly stimulating story of dance and love between two men is being adapted into a live-action Netflix Film! 

The story follows two men: Shinya Suzuki (Ryoma Takeuchi), Japan’s Latin dance champion, and Shinya Sugiki (Keita Machida), often called "Emperor," Japan’s ballroom dance champion and ranked second in the world. One day, Sugiki appears before Suzuki and proposes that the two of them become champions of the 10 Dance: an extremely demanding competition that requires both physical and mental fortitude, as participants must master 10 styles of dance — five Latin and five ballroom — and perform them all in a single day. Suzuki and Sugiki commence training at Sugiki Dance School accompanied by their respective dance partners, Aki Tajima (Shiori Doi) and Fusako Yagami (Anna Ishii). The two men clash as a result of their conflicting lifestyles and personalities, yet as they begin to understand each other’s style of dance, they find themselves drawn closer to one another.

The Netflix Film "10DANCE" starts streaming worldwide on Thursday, December 18, 2025, only on Netflix.

Starring: Ryoma Takeuchi, Keita Machida
Shiori Doi, Anna Ishii, Shinya Hamada, Oshiro Maeda
Nadiya Bychkova, Susie Trayling, Pasquale La Rocca
Based on the manga "10 DANCE" by Inouesatoh (serialized in Weekly Young Magazine by Kodansha)
Directed by Keishi Otomo
https://www.netflix.com/10DANCE
